definition: to hand in one's examination script
to hand over/to deliver/to pay (money)/to turn over/to make friends/to intersect (lines)/variant of 跤[jiao1]
scroll/book/volume/chapter/examination paper/classifier for books, paintings: volume, scroll
to roll up/roll/classifier for small rolled things (wad of paper money, movie reel etc)

sentences.english: Check your papers carefully before handing them in.
sentences.chinese: 在交卷之前，仔細檢查你的試卷。

sentences.english: " Outlaws" with a launch is approaching 2 grades hand.
sentences.chinese: 《水滸傳》以一開播便逼近2的成績交卷。

sentences.english: He only finished what he knew and left the rest blank.
sentences.chinese: 他把會做的做完就交卷了，不會的全空下來。

sentences.english: Two hours were allowed for the final examination.
sentences.chinese: 期中考試限兩小時交卷。

sentences.english: Do you know who handed the math paper in first this time?
sentences.chinese: 你知道這次數學考試誰第一個交卷的嗎？

sentences.english: I made it clear to them that they must hand in their papers before 10 o’clock in the morning.
sentences.chinese: 我向他們講清楚了的，他們必須在上午十時前交卷。

sentences.english: She checked all her answers before turning in her test.
sentences.chinese: 交卷之前她檢查了一遍答案。

sentences.english: Totally satisfied, I handed my test in feeling like I had aced it.
sentences.chinese: 我感覺非常得意，交卷了以後覺得我考得特好。

sentences.english: Must we hand in our papers now?
My ”knowledge” emptied the moment I handed in those exam.
sentences.chinese: 我的“知識”在交卷的時候已經全部用完了。

sentences.english: Your answers on the test paper, I write a segment of words.
sentences.chinese: 臨交卷時，我在試卷上寫下了一段話。

sentences.english: Go over your papers carefully before you hand them in.
sentences.chinese: 交卷之前，請認真從頭到尾看一遍。

sentences.english: I complete an assignment in the afternoon the speed is quicker.
sentences.chinese: 下午我交卷的速度更快。

definition: exam candidate/student whose name has been put forward for an exam
to correct student papers/to grade exam papers
an examiner/an official conducting an exam
